    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> coriander</strong> roughly</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>crushed garlic </strong>and <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bash into a smooth paste</p><p>Stir the <strong>coriander paste </strong>through your<strong> soured cream</strong> – this is your <strong>enchiladas suizas sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don't have a pestle & mortar, chop the coriander very finely and mix with the salt and sour cream in a bowl!</p>",
